  "prompt": "Once I've installed Windows 10, if I have to factory reset my laptop, will it revert to Windows 8.1 or stay on Windows 10?",
  "response": "If you factory reset your laptop after installing Windows 10, it will stay on Windows 10. The factory reset process in Windows 10 will restore the system to its original state, but it will not revert the operating system to a previous version such as Windows 8.1. The reset will reinstall Windows 10, removing personal files, settings, and installed apps, effectively giving you a fresh installation of Windows 10.",
